Interface MultiPartGetMessageCallback

    • Method Detail

      • handleOkResponse

        Map<String,Object> handleOkResponse(OutMessage outMessage,
                                  File multiPartFile)
        Subclasses wishing to get a handle of the ok response from a MultiPartGetMessage, must write code in this method.
        Parameters:
        outMessage - the OutMessage instance for which this callback is called
        multiPartFile - the File object that represents the complete multi part file downloaded from the server.
        Returns:
        map of missing object names and the missing objects, indicating whether the message processing is completely done or no.

        Note : Returning a non empty map to the SimplyReliableInfra implies that after this, the callback object will be responsible to indicate the completion of this message processing to the SimplyReliableInfra API. Make sure that you do that as it can lead to un desired conditions!!
